   is a matrix with entries in C such that

The *-subalgebra, C0, of C, which is generated by the matrix elements of u, is dense in C;There exists a C*-algebra homomorphism called the comultiplication Δ: C → C ⊗ C (where C ⊗ C is the C*-algebra tensor product - the completion of the algebraic tensor product of C and C) such that for all i, j we have:
  
    
      
